{
  "stem": "3964.3",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But it was a life where you still had your family, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] where you had an opportunity to associate with other people, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] where you had a lot of information coming in through the grapevine, what was going on everywhere, including the rest of the world, because the Latvian Jews would go out to Riga and do the same or similar work we were doing.",
      "word_count": 71
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Those people had lived in Riga and they still had a lot of contacts.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Not only did they have contacts, but they were able to organize groups we were-- which were able to bring food into the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And as I said earlier, as much as there was anger at first amongst the Latvian Jewish people who were left in the ghetto, in their ghetto, against the German Jews, slowly this relationship really thawed out and warmed up.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And it became a really good relationship.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Number one, there were very few women in the Latvian ghettos, and they were mostly men.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Most of the German men, German Jewish men who had come into the ghetto were taken out of the ghetto and working outside the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "A lot of young, young Jewish women, young girls.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And the Latvian men who had had families and those who didn't have families were yearning for a relationship of some kind, a human relationship, whatever it entails, you know, emotional, physical.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And the bond between the Latvian ghetto, Latvian Jews and the German Jews, just because of that kind of a need for each other, became very strong very quickly.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And it was a good relationship.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, I remember after-- it must've been in middle of 1942, a young man, his name was Hirszke Kliksman.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
